HEADWORD: Nocake
<hw>No"cake</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr. Indian
<ets>nookhik</ets> meal. <au>Palfrey.</au>]</ety> <def>Indian corn
parched, and beaten to powder, -- used for food by the Northern American
Indians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

